---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Dispensary Business Plan | Maine Dispensary Guide" 
  description="Complete guide to creating a business plan for your Maine cannabis dispensary. Includes template, financial projections, and essential sections."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1454165804606-c3d57bc86b40?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1200&h=400"
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Dispensary Business Plan</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Your complete guide to creating a comprehensive business plan for a Maine cannabis dispensary</p>
    </div>

    <section>
      <h2>Why You Need a Business Plan</h2>
      <p>A well-crafted business plan is essential for any Maine dispensary. It serves multiple purposes: securing funding, guiding operations, and demonstrating to regulators that you have a viable, professional approach to your business.</p>
      <p>Whether you're seeking investment, applying for a loan, or simply organizing your thoughts, a business plan is your roadmap to success in Maine's cannabis market.</p>
    </section>

    <Callout title="Designing Your Success" type="passion">
      Your business plan is more than just a document—it's the first tangible version of your dream. Writing it down makes your vision real and gives you the confidence to lead. It's the moment you stop "thinking" about a dispensary and start "building" one.
    </Callout>

    <section>
      <h2>Essential Sections</h2>
      
      <h3>1. Executive Summary</h3>
      <p>This is the first section but should be written last. Summarize your business concept, goals, financial requirements, and expected ROI. Keep it to one page.</p>
      
      <h3>2. Company Description</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Business name and legal structure (LLC, corporation, etc.)</li>
        <li>Mission statement</li>
        <li>Location (specific Maine city/town)</li>
        <li>License type (retail, medical, or both)</li>
        <li>Ownership and management team</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h3>3. Market Analysis</h3>
      <p>Research Maine's cannabis market thoroughly:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Total addressable market size</li>
        <li>Projected growth rate</li>
        <li>Competitive landscape (other dispensaries in your area)</li>
        <li>Target customer demographics</li>
        <li>Market trends and opportunities</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h3>4. Products and Services</h3>
      <p>Detail what you'll sell:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Flower (various strains)</li>
        <li>Concentrates (wax, shatter, rosin)</li>
        <li>Edibles</li>
        <li>Tinctures and topicals</li>
        <li>Accessories</li>
        <li>Delivery services (if licensed)</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h3>5. Marketing Strategy</h3>
      <p>Maine has specific marketing restrictions. Include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Brand positioning</li>
        <li>Customer acquisition channels</li>
        <li>Loyalty programs</li>
        <li>Local marketing efforts</li>
        <li>Compliance with Maine advertising rules</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h3>6. Operations Plan</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Day-to-day operations</li>
        <li>Technology systems (POS, seed-to-sale)</li>
        <li>Supplier relationships</li>
        <li>Security protocols</li>
        <li>Quality control</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h3>7. Financial Projections</h3>
      <p>This is what investors care about most:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Startup costs breakdown</li>
        <li>3-year revenue projections</li>
        <li>Operating expense budget</li>
        <li>Cash flow projections</li>
        <li>Break-even analysis</li>
        <li>ROI timeline</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Financial Snapshot: Maine Dispensary</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Category</th>
            <th>Estimated Cost</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>License & Fees</td>
            <td>$3,000 - $15,000</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Real Estate (build-out)</td>
            <td>$100,000 - $300,000</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Security Systems</td>
            <td>$25,000 - $75,000</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Initial Inventory</td>
            <td>$50,000 - $150,000</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>POS & Technology</td>
            <td>$10,000 - $30,000</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Working Capital (6 months)</td>
            <td>$100,000 - $250,000</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Total Investment</strong></td>
            <td><strong>$300,000 - $850,000</strong></td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Key Takeaways</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>A business plan is essential for funding and operations</li>
        <li>Include detailed financial projections</li>
        <li>Research Maine's specific market conditions</li>
        <li>Document your compliance procedures</li>
        <li>Be realistic about timelines and costs</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>Further Reading</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.sba.gov/business-guide/plan-your-business/write-your-business-plan" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">SBA Guide: Write your business plan</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em>This information is for informational purposes only and does not constitute legal or financial advice. Consult with qualified professionals in Maine for specific guidance.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2 { margin-top: 0; }
  section h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
  th, td { padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  th { background: var(--color-background); }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; }
  .further-reading { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.05); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .further-reading h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
</style>
